column5: NICE!!! Pretty soon we won't have any either at this rate. It's morning,but it's already 57 degrees Farenheit. I guess I'll have to go to the arctic circle to try ice fishing. Greencoachdog,catch a 10lb bass today and post the pic for everyone here who is "jones'n". Good luck "dog".
There will be ice in your Pina' Colada. Don't choke on the umbrella, fella.
~~~The only ice you'll be looken for is in the branch water, you use to soften the Shine you been a drinken
Why did you spill yer drink in the lake
In that first pic, is dat a Sudden Wall-ice?
Nice G, now git yer behind up here and fish like the rest of us, cold and wet like God intended ice fishing to be  Joey
Nice Sheepy Glen did you kidnap that when you were in the Bay of Quinte in November
LOL...great report...  Loved the MTP comment at the end.  Great to see some softwater reports Glen....we've been teased here lately with +16C weather!!!!
